The board of SAA will brief the media on the resignation of their CEO Vuyani Jarana. JOHANNESBURG – Zuks Ramasia has been appointed Acting South African Airways CEO. Ramasia replaces Vuyani Jarana who resigned last week. Jarana was appointed to head the embattled airline in November 2017. READ: Moody's warns of SA recession Ramasia was previously SAA's General Manager of Operations. The ailing airline says it will conduct a national and international search for someone to fill in the position.